al literature, from the German founders of art history as an academic discipline to Heidegger, Derrida, and de Man, Minor considers the issue through a series of Baroque masterpieces: Bernini’s Baldacchino in St. Peter’s Basilica, the statues in the church of San Giovanni in Laterano, Borromini’s church of Sant’Ivo alla Sapienza, Baciccio’s frescoes in the church of Il Gesù, the paintings of Philippe de Champaigne, and the Corsini Chapel in San Giovanni in Laterano.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aAesthetics, Modernx17th century. 0aAesthetics, Modernx18th century. 0aAesthetics, Moderny17th century. 0aAesthetics, Moderny18th century. 0aArt criticismxHistoryxItalyxHistory. 0aArt criticismxHistory. 0aArts, BaroquexItaly. 0aArts, BaroquezItaly. 0aArts, Italianx17th century. 0aArts, Italianx18th century. 0aArts, Italiany17th century. 0aArts, Italiany18th century. 7aART / History / Baroque & Rococo.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311060681240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144261769840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442617698423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442617698.jpg  a978-3-11-060681-2  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles